1353
00:53:35,377 --> 00:53:37,677
    Narrator: Tucked away       
    up Connecticut Avenue       

1354
00:53:37,679 --> 00:53:39,779
    sits Bistrot du Coin.       

1355
00:53:39,781 --> 00:53:42,048
    An energetic crowd          
    has gathered,               

1356
00:53:42,050 --> 00:53:44,918
    enjoying French classics    
    like steamed mussels        

1357
00:53:44,920 --> 00:53:46,619
        and steak frites.       

1358
00:53:48,290 --> 00:53:51,191
        Woman: We love the food.
         We love the atmosphere.

1359
00:53:51,193 --> 00:53:52,959
        We love the environment.
        It's just...            

1360
00:53:52,961 --> 00:53:54,761
            It's just           
            a fantastic place.  

1361
00:53:54,763 --> 00:53:56,796
The drinks are good.            
 The lights are low.            

1362
00:53:56,798 --> 00:53:58,264
        [Sizzling]              

1363
00:53:58,266 --> 00:53:59,999
    Man: It's not               
    sophisticated food,         

1364
00:54:00,001 --> 00:54:01,735
        but it's nice,          
        hearty food.            

1365
00:54:01,737 --> 00:54:04,070
        This is the thing       
        I would have at home.   

1366
00:54:04,072 --> 00:54:06,005
                Bon appetit.    

1367
00:54:06,007 --> 00:54:09,709
 It's a typical French bistro,  
but with a different ambiance.  

1368
00:54:09,711 --> 00:54:11,644
 It's French, fun, and friendly.

1369
00:54:11,646 --> 00:54:13,246
        That's our model.       

1370
00:54:13,248 --> 00:54:17,350
            Woman: The food is  
            really the best     
            food in town,       

1371
00:54:17,352 --> 00:54:20,653
            and it's a busy,    
            warm environment.   

1372
00:54:20,655 --> 00:54:23,056
Joe Dassin: ♪ Je m'baladais     
      sur l'avenue ♪            

1373
00:54:23,058 --> 00:54:25,792
♪ Le coeur ouvert à l'inconnu,  
         j'avais... ♪           

1374
00:54:25,794 --> 00:54:27,394
 Man: This is probably          
the best place in D.C.          

1375
00:54:27,396 --> 00:54:30,764
where you can find              
 great wines at a               
fairly cheap price,             

1376
00:54:30,766 --> 00:54:32,565
which is unusual.               

1377
00:54:32,567 --> 00:54:36,202
Narrator: But it's the steamed  
  mussels that keep customers   
         coming back.           

1378
00:54:36,204 --> 00:54:38,071
    The Bistrot's secret?       

1379
00:54:38,073 --> 00:54:40,840
You have to start with          
a great quality of mussel.      

1380
00:54:40,842 --> 00:54:43,143
We get delivery every day.      

1381
00:54:43,145 --> 00:54:45,812
    Because of the volume       
we go through, nothing stays.   

1382
00:54:45,814 --> 00:54:48,281
     [People talking loudly;    
         music playing]         

1383
00:54:48,283 --> 00:54:51,751
    Narrator: 3 times a year,   
    the Bistrot kicks           
    into overdrive,             

1384
00:54:51,753 --> 00:54:54,254
    throws a party              
    you won't soon forget.      

1385
00:54:54,256 --> 00:54:56,723
     Tonight, when the clock    
     strikes midnight,          

1386
00:54:56,725 --> 00:54:59,159
    this year's vintage         
of Beaujolais Nouveau wine      

1387
00:54:59,161 --> 00:55:01,528
can officially be uncorked.     

1388
00:55:01,530 --> 00:55:05,031
         [Music playing]        

1389
00:55:05,033 --> 00:55:08,201
Singer: ♪ ...in the street ♪    

1390
00:55:08,203 --> 00:55:10,703
Felix: Tonight, we celebrate    
the new one of the year,        

1391
00:55:10,705 --> 00:55:13,206
     and it's a crazy party.    

1392
00:55:13,208 --> 00:55:17,210
 It's more like a tradition that
 we give back to our customer.  

1393
00:55:17,212 --> 00:55:20,246
    All year long, they come    
         and support us,        

1394
00:55:20,248 --> 00:55:23,283
and with Beaujolais Nouveau,    
        we go crazy.            

1395
00:55:23,285 --> 00:55:25,485
        So, we give away        
        a lot of bottle.        

1396
00:55:25,487 --> 00:55:28,288
     I cannot tell how much,    
         but it's a lot.        

1397
00:55:28,290 --> 00:55:30,557
    And then we put             
    everybody on UBER!          

